From: Wojciech Drewek <wojciech.drewek@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 4 Jun 2024 14:55:14 +0200
Subject: ice: implement AQ download pkg retry
Patch-mainline: v6.10-rc5
Git-commit: a27f6ac9d404ea84196639dcc456f969ef813c0f
References: git-fixes

ice_aqc_opc_download_pkg (0x0C40) AQ sporadically returns error due
to FW issue. Fix this by retrying five times before moving to
Safe Mode. Sleep for 20 ms before retrying. This was tested with the
4.40 firmware.

Fixes: c76488109616 ("ice: Implement Dynamic Device Personalization (DDP) download")
Reviewed-by: Michal Swiatkowski <michal.swiatkowski@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Wojciech Drewek <wojciech.drewek@intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Brett Creeley <brett.creeley@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Przemek Kitszel <przemyslaw.kitszel@intel.com>
Tested-by: Pucha Himasekhar Reddy <himasekharx.reddy.pucha@intel.com> (A Contingent worker at Intel)
Signed-off-by: Tony Nguyen <anthony.l.nguyen@intel.com>
Acked-by: Thomas Bogendoerfer <tbogendoerfer@suse.de>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_ddp.c |   23 +++++++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_ddp.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ice/ice_ddp.c
@@ -1329,6 +1329,7 @@ ice_dwnld_cfg_bufs_no_lock(struct ice_hw
 
 	for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
 		bool last = false;
+		int try_cnt = 0;
 		int status;
 
 		bh = (struct ice_buf_hdr *)(bufs + start + i);
@@ -1336,8 +1337,26 @@ ice_dwnld_cfg_bufs_no_lock(struct ice_hw
 		if (indicate_last)
 			last = ice_is_last_download_buffer(bh, i, count);
 
-		status = ice_aq_download_pkg(hw, bh, ICE_PKG_BUF_SIZE, last,
-					     &offset, &info, NULL);
+		while (1) {
+			status = ice_aq_download_pkg(hw, bh, ICE_PKG_BUF_SIZE,
+						     last, &offset, &info,
+						     NULL);
+			if (hw->adminq.sq_last_status != ICE_AQ_RC_ENOSEC &&
+			    hw->adminq.sq_last_status != ICE_AQ_RC_EBADSIG)
+				break;
+
+			try_cnt++;
+
+			if (try_cnt == 5)
+				break;
+
+			msleep(20);
+		}
+
+		if (try_cnt)
+			dev_dbg(ice_hw_to_dev(hw),
+				"ice_aq_download_pkg number of retries: %d\n",
+				try_cnt);
 
 		/* Save AQ status from download package */
 		if (status) {
